  "instructions": [
    "Wash and cut the beef tomatoes into bite-size chunks and set aside.",
    "In a Korean brass bowl, heat sesame oil over medium heat and sauté garlic, ginger, and sliced shiitake mushrooms until fragrant.",
    "Add the diced tofu, julienned carrot, and green onion to the bowl, stirring for 2 minutes.",
    "Pour in 800ml of water, bring to a gentle boil, then reduce to a simmer.",
    "Stir in miso paste, soy sauce, rice vinegar, and sriracha; let the mixture simmer for 10 minutes to meld flavors.",
    "Add the chopped tomatoes, letting them cook until soft and the broth thickens slightly, about 8 minutes.",
    "Taste and adjust seasoning; if needed, add more sriracha for heat or soy sauce for depth.",
    "Transfer the stew to individual bowls, garnish with chopped cilantro and seaweed flakes, and serve hot."
  ],
